<subSubSection id="5CF6589A920DFFCAFF08FBA6ED3CF945" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" type="description">
<paragraph id="14530B11920DFFCAFF08FBA6ED55FBE6" blockId="10.[130,777,1077,1772]" box="[132,277,1077,1103]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B11920DFFCAFF08FBC7ED3CF945" blockId="10.[130,777,1077,1772]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">
Colony erect, consisting of cylindrical branches, complete bifurcations not observed, probably articulated during life. Branches 8- to 10-serial, longest observed branch 
<quantity id="D314A6F4920DFFCAFD26FB07EF44FB07" box="[682,772,1172,1198]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
, branch width 
<quantity id="D314A6F4920DFFCAFE97FB27EDF8FB67" box="[283,440,1204,1230]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.15" metricValueMax="6.1" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" unit="mm" value="0.515" valueMax="0.61" valueMin="0.42">0.42-0.61 mm</quantity>
wide increasing to about 
<quantity id="D314A6F4920DFFCAFD44FB27EF48FB67" box="[712,776,1204,1230]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
when fertile zooids are present. Colony base unknown. Autozooids longer than wide, ZL 395-526 µm (N colonies 2; N zooids 8; mean 439 µm; SD 43 µm), ZW 184-211 µm (N colonies 2; N zooids 8; mean 194 µm; SD 14 µm), elongate hexagonal. Frontal wall cryptocystal, margins raised, centre depressed, smooth textured; cryptocystal pores lacking; single pair of opesiules located proximolaterally of orifice within depressed central part of cryptocyst, longitudinally elliptical, some with a transverse bar subdividing the opening internally. Orifice subcircular, 94-118 µm in diameter, sometimes with a slight proximal embayment, rim salient. Fertile autozooids clustered, ooecia helmet shaped, about 220 µm long by 200-240 µm wide, calcification smooth, continuous with the cryptocyst of the distal zooid, orifice of ovicellate zooids round, slightly larger than those of non-ovicellate zooids, about 120-150 µm long by 140-160 µm wide. Mandibulate polymorphs unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5CF6589A920DFFCAFF08F881E823F9A4" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="14530B11920DFFCAFF08F881ECA8F885" blockId="10.[131,775,1810,2028]" box="[132,232,1810,1836]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B11920DFFCAFF08F8A2E845FB07" blockId="10.[131,775,1810,2028]" lastBlockId="10.[810,1456,1076,1549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">
This species was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920DFFCAFE5FF8A1EE3FF8E5" author="DUCASSE J." box="[467,639,1841,1868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" refId="ref7196" refString="DUCASSE J. 1958. - Les Bryozoaires maestrichtiens et campaniens de la Saintonge et du Perigord occidental, repartition et valeur stratigraphique. Travaux scientifiques du Centre de Geologie Approfondie, Universite de Bordeaux, 168 p." type="book" year="1958">Ducasse (1958)</bibRefCitation>
in her thesis as 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFF2FF8C1EDC2F8C2" authorityName="Ducasse" authorityYear="1958" box="[163,386,1873,1899]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crestulata">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFF2FF8C1EDC2F8C2" box="[163,386,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">Micropora crestulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although it is clearly congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFF30F8E2EDD4F822" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[188,404,1905,1931]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFF30F8E2EDD4F822" box="[188,404,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">Dimorphomicropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it was not mentioned in the publication of 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920DFFCAFF71F801EE78F805" author="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M." box="[253,568,1937,1964]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" pagination="155 - 157" refId="ref7235" refString="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M. 1960. - Dimorphomicropora: nouveau genre de bryozoaire cheilostome du Maestrichtien du bassin aquitain. Compte Rendu de la Societe geologique de France 6: 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1960">Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux (1960)</bibRefCitation>
when introducing this genus. Most specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFE5AF821EE1EF862" authorityName="Ducasse" authorityYear="1958" box="[470,606,1969,1995]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crestulata">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFE5AF821EE1EF862" box="[470,606,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. crestulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
come from the Aubeterre Formation in coastal localities south of Royan where 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFCF4FBA6EF9AFBE7" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[888,986,1077,1102]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="voigti">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFCF4FBA6EF9AFBE7" box="[888,986,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. voigti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs. However, the 
<typeStatus id="CB57B5B3920DFFCAFA82FBA6E97DFBE6" box="[1294,1341,1077,1103]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">type</typeStatus>
specimen is slightly older having been collected by 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920DFFCAFA8EFBC6E9EFFBC6" author="DUCASSE J." box="[1282,1455,1108,1135]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" refId="ref7196" refString="DUCASSE J. 1958. - Les Bryozoaires maestrichtiens et campaniens de la Saintonge et du Perigord occidental, repartition et valeur stratigraphique. Travaux scientifiques du Centre de Geologie Approfondie, Universite de Bordeaux, 168 p." type="book" year="1958">Ducasse (1958)</bibRefCitation>
from an inland site at Mirambeau which exposes the Barbezieux Formation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B11920DFFCAFCCFFB27E823F9A4" blockId="10.[810,1456,1076,1549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">
The subcircular orifice of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFBC2FB26E890FB67" authorityName="Ducasse" authorityYear="1958" box="[1102,1232,1204,1230]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crestulata">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFBC2FB26E890FB67" box="[1102,1232,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. crestulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
allows this species to be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFB82FB47E824FB44" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[1038,1124,1236,1261]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="voigti">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFB82FB47E824FB44" box="[1038,1124,1236,1261]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. voigti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Scanning electron micrographs of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFCC7FB67EFEFFAA4" box="[843,943,1268,1293]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="rugica">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFCC7FB67EFEFFAA4" box="[843,943,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. rugica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
kindly provided by Oliver Kesselhut (Aachen) show similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFB95FA87E8DBFA84" authorityName="Ducasse" authorityYear="1958" box="[1049,1179,1299,1325]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crestulata">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFB95FA87E8DBFA84" box="[1049,1179,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. crestulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, this Maastrichtian species sometimes has a lip extending over the proximal edge of the orifice, a feature not seen in 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFB6FFAC7E938FAC4" baseAuthorityName="Ducasse" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[1251,1400,1363,1389]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crustulenta">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFB6FFAC7E938FAC4" box="[1251,1400,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. crustulenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The poorly preserved 
<typeStatus id="CB57B5B3920DFFCAFC53FAE0E87FFA24" box="[991,1087,1395,1421]" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFBD7FAE7EF2BFA07" authority="(d'Orbigny, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFBD7FAE7E96DFA24" box="[1115,1325,1396,1421]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">Micropora transversa</emphasis>
(d’Orbigny, 1851)
</taxonomicName>
from the Upper Maastrichtian of Contentin is possibly a senior synonym of either 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFBC4FA27E88AFA64" authorityName="Ducasse" authorityYear="1958" box="[1096,1226,1459,1485]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crestulata">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFBC4FA27E88AFA64" box="[1096,1226,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. crestulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFB67FA27E90CFA64" box="[1259,1356,1460,1485]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="rugica">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFB67FA27E90CFA64" box="[1259,1356,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">D. rugica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but better material of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920DFFCAFC42FA47E81AFA44" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[974,1114,1492,1517]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="523" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis id="2698D703920DFFCAFC42FA47E81AFA44" box="[974,1114,1492,1517]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="523">M. transversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed before either of these synonymies can be accepted.
</paragraph>
